    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> there is no live examples yet. The getting started of the helper have its samples on codepen, but I'm not sure we want to go this. What do you suggest?\n\nAs for the live examples, we need to have them also for the widget examples (#1238)\n\nOne possible solution is to use https://github.com/react-toolbox/react-toolbox/blob/dea14144b8969eca748d4899fb05bc8c52734a31/docs/app/components/preview/index.js (babel-standalone).\n\nBasically we would need to create a small Preview component that would take the code sample (that can be obtained via .innerText on a `<code>` block in DOM) then transform that with babel-standalone, injecting the right context (basically every InstantSearch export) and render it. This is what the react toolbox preview does\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
